The paper deals with signal recovery from measurements, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of expectation propagation (EP) is a common technique in signal processing (cs.SP) and the analysis of the algorithm's performance involves large system limits, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also mentions the use of the Haar matrix, which is a topic in matrix theory (cs.MM).
